vings per bottle | Cost per serving: ~$0.60 | The price is competitive for a pure algae omega-3 with both DHA and EPA. Good value compared to similar products in the market. | | 6 | **Compare with Top Brands** | Nordic Naturals, iwi Life, Feel, etc. | Similar or lower DHA/EPA per serving | Nordic Naturals and iwi Life offer similar or slightly higher doses per serving but at a higher price point. Nested Naturals is a solid mid-tier choice for value and purity. | | 7 | **Suitability for Vagus Nerve Support** | 300mg omega-3 (DHA/EPA) | Daily support for vagal tone | Research shows omega-3s can support vagus nerve activity and heart rate variability. This product is a safe, effective option for that purpose, especially if you want a clean, vegan alternative. | | 8 | **Monetization/Conversion Notes** | Affiliate links, education content, bundles | Higher conversion via clean ingredient messaging | Positioning this product as \\\"vegan, pure, and third-party tested\\\" appeals to health-conscious and plant-based consumers. Bundling with other nerve-support nutrients or educational content can increase your average order value. | --- ### **Summary Recommendation:** **Nested Naturals Vegan Omega-3** is a reputable, affordable, and effective algae-based omega-3 supplement for supporting vagus nerve health. It contains both DHA and EPA at doses shown in studies to benefit heart rate variability and overall nervous system resilience. While not the highest-potency option, it is well-balanced for daily use and ideal for anyone seeking a vegan, allergen-free, clean-label supplement. If you want maximum effect for the vagus nerve and are open to a higher daily dose, you could double up (take 4 softgels/day) to match top-tier brands, but for most people, the standard dose is appropriate. --- #### **Why This Recommendation?** - **Science-backed:** Algae DHA/EPA is shown to support vagal tone and HRV. - **Clean and safe:** No fishy taste, no toxins, allergen-free, vegan. - **Good v